<b><font class="print-title">What could make you quit EQ?</font></b><br /><br />
<font class="print-sub">Articles / Luclin News<br />
<b>Date:</b> Jan 08, 2003 - 01:34 PM</font>
</td></tr>
<tr><td>
<font class="print-normal"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=85250">Shjekai</a> &lt;<a href="http://pub103.ezboard.com/bhouseofcommons">House of Commons</a>&gt; has hit on an interesting topic that has drawn some interesting responses. The question posed is &quot;What would make you quit? We've all heard the endless bitching about EQ customer service or about millions of nerfs and all the threats of quitting and such. Honstly though, what would make you quit? What would have to happen, regarding the game only, to make you quit. Being bored or finding something better to do is not what I am looking for. I'm talking about wanting to play but being way to pissed off or dissapointed to continue.&quot; To engage in this discussion or to see what the opinions on the subject are, <a href="http://pub106.ezboard.com/fluclin71335general.showMessage?topicID=9367.topic">click here</a>!<br /><br />
